<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 5:02AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF LIGHT FREEZING DRIZZLE THROUGH THE MORNING COMMUTE...
Light drizzle and surface temperatures right at the freezing mark
are resulting in areas of light freezing drizzle this morning. A
few localized slick spots may develop on roadways, especially
bridges and overpasses. Drivers are urged to use caution during
the morning commute. Temperatures are expected to climb above
freezing across all of southeast Michigan by around 9 am bringing
an end to any hazardous travel.</description>
